Iavan Pijoos, News24(iStock) Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Polokwane &ndash; Nine people were killed and seven seriously injured when a truck and a taxi collided head-on along the R579 in Limpopo on Tuesday morning, police said.The victims, three women and six men, were all in the minibus, Lieutenant Colonel Moatshe Ngoepe said.They were on their way to Lebowakgomo from Ga-Masemola when the accident happened around 07:00.The truck driver and his assistant sustained minor injuries. Police are investigating a case of culpable homicide.Nine people have been killed in a head on collision outside Lebowakgomo in Limpopo. Seven others critically injured #sabcnews pic.twitter.com/7QD1Jt8euV&mdash; Shibu Mamokgere (@shiburyder) June 6, 2017Nine people have been killed in a head on collision outside Lebowakgomo in Limpopo. Seven others critically injured #sabcnews pic.twitter.com/7QD1Jt8euVFollow News24 reporter Iavan Pijoos on Twitter for the latest updates: @Iavan13&nbsp;24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.